The paper discusses methods for explaining predictions in nonlinear models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper mentions deep neural networks, which are a type of neural network commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and speech recognition, suggesting cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses regression and classification applications, which are also relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
